Class PSLocator

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSKey
      com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSLocator
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, Serializable, Cloneable
public class PSLocator
extends PSKey
implements Serializable

A container that holds an object locator, e.g. for content items this will be the contentid and revision.

PSLocator

public PSLocator()
Creates an empty locator object. This is used for creating a new component that has not been saved to the database.

PSLocator

public PSLocator(int id,
                 int revision)
Constructs a new locator for the supplied id and revision. The constructed object is persisted.

revision - the locator revision, -1 means undefined.

PSLocator

public PSLocator(String id)
Convenience constructor {#link PSLocator(String, String)} with an undefined revision. The constructed object is default to persisted.

Parameters:
id - the locator id. It may not be null or empty. It must be a parsable int and >= 0.

PSLocator

public PSLocator(String id,
                 String revision)
Constructs a new locator for the supplied id and revision. The constructed object is persisted.

Parameters:
id - the locator id. It may not be null or empty. It must be a parsable int and >= 0.
revision - the locator revision, may be null.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the supplied id is invalid.
NumberFormatException - if the supplied id is not a parsable int.
